  "description": "A multicenter interictal intracranial electroencephalography (iEEG) dataset from patients with epilepsy, comprising de-identified recordings from three major medical centers (NIH, Johns Hopkins Hospital, and University of Miami). The dataset includes annotated sleep/awake states and processed derivatives for source-sink connectivity and high-frequency oscillation analyses. Note: This represents a subset of the full multicenter study; additional data from Kansas University Medical Center, University of Pittsburgh Medical Center, and Cleveland Clinic are not included due to data sharing restrictions at those institutions. Complementary ictal recordings from overlapping subjects are available in ds003029.",
  "methods_description": "Intracranial EEG recordings were collected from epilepsy patients across multiple centers. Data was converted to BIDS format using MNE-BIDS. Processed derivatives include source-sink connectivity analysis and high-frequency oscillation (HFO) detection using both RMS and Hilbert transform methods.",
